        <abstract>
            <p>Sends a query he would like GHD to put to Clerk Maxwell: why does a sponged leaf dry more rapidly, although sponging cannot remove the waxy bloom from the minute pores through which it is secreted?</p>
            <p>Is very glad to hear about tides in the earth.</p>
        </abstract>
